<paragraph blockId="6.[151,752,465,525]" box="[151,323,500,525]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,274,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
Figs 
<number box="[215,274,500,524]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="9.75" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[285,314,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">50</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,572,848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
A single male was collected in 
<number box="[514,570,572,596]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="2014.0">2014</number>
while perched on the underside of a leaf about six meters from the ground around 
<number box="[236,265,607,632]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="16.0">16</number>
:00h.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,572,848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
Apparently this species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[733,781,645,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">type</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[796,1047,644,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott 
<number box="[988,1047,644,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and the specimen collected at the 
<collectionCode box="[151,223,680,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">PNSD</collectionCode>
is the second record for the species in the last 
<number box="[749,791,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="125.0">125</number>
years. As noticed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[1036,1305,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number box="[1237,1297,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number box="[280,338,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
misidentify a new species described below as 
<taxonomicName box="[872,992,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[872,992,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1000,1090,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1000,1090,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[1155,1300,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalfreda">
<emphasis box="[1155,1300,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. amalfreda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the size of these species is similar; however, the large black areas on both wings upperside and the longer and larger subapical blue patch on forewing upperside of 
<taxonomicName box="[674,819,788,813]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalfreda">
<emphasis box="[674,819,788,813]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. amalfreda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily used to distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName box="[1276,1396,788,813]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1276,1396,788,813]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="6" pageNumber="233" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
